    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public JSValue invoke(JSObject instance,
                      java.lang.Object... args)
        Executes JavaScript function and returns result of execution as JSValue. This method blocks current thread execution until JavaScript function finishes its execution. If JavaScript function raises an exception, then JSFunctionException with error message that describes the reason of the exception will be thrown. Same error message will be printed in JavaScript Console. To get messages from JavaScript Console use ConsoleListener.
        执行JavaScript函数并以JSValue返回执行结果。此方法将阻止当前线程执行，直到JavaScript函数完成执行为止。如果JavaScript函数引发异常，则将引发JSFunctionException，并显示描述异常原因的错误消息。同样的错误消息将在JavaScript控制台中打印。要从JavaScript控制台获取消息，请使用ConsoleListener。
        Parameters:
        instance - JavaScript object the underlying function is invoked from. Pass null to invoke function as a global function. -调用底层函数的JavaScript对象。将调用函数作为全局函数传递。
        args - input arguments. -输入参数。
        Returns:
        result of JavaScript function execution. Never returns null. JavaScript函数执行的结果。永不归还。
        Throws:
        JSFunctionException - when exception occurs during function execution.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when instance is a valid JavaScript object, but it belongs to a different JavaScript execution context. The instance must be running in the same execution context as the current function.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when args parameters contain unsupported type.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when instance is already disposed or its JavaScript execution context isn't available anymore.

      • invokeAsync

        public java.util.concurrent.Future<JSValue> invokeAsync(JSObject instance,
                                                        java.lang.Object... args)
        Executes JavaScript function and returns result of execution as Future<JSValue>. This method doesn't blocks current thread execution and is invoked asynchronously changing result state depending on JavaScript function execution status. If JavaScript function executes successfully, the result status will be set to "Done" and might be checked invoking the Future.isDone() method of the result instance. If JavaScript function execution has failed due to some reason, then the result status will be set to "Done" and might be checked invoking the Future.isDone() method of the result instance. In this case invoking the Future.get() method will throw the ExecutionException containing information about the failure. The error message that describes the reason of the exception will be printed in JavaScript Console. To get messages from JavaScript Console use ConsoleListener.
        执行JavaScript函数并以Future 返回执行结果。此方法不阻止当前线程执行，而是根据JavaScript函数执行状态异步调用以更改结果状态。如果JavaScript函数成功执行，则结果状态将设置为“完成”，并且可以调用结果实例的Future.isDone（）方法进行检查。如果由于某种原因JavaScript函数执行失败，则结果状态将设置为“完成”，并可以调用结果实例的Future.isDone（）方法进行检查。在这种情况下，调用Future.get（）方法将抛出ExecutionException，其中包含有关失败的信息。描述异常原因的错误消息将在JavaScript控制台中打印。要从JavaScript控制台获取消息，请使用ConsoleListener。
        Parameters:
        instance - JavaScript object the underlying function is invoked from. Pass null to invoke function as a global function. -调用底层函数的JavaScript对象。将调用函数作为全局函数传递。
        args - input arguments. -输入参数。
        Returns:
        Future<JSValue> instance that might contain result of JavaScript function execution. Never returns null. 实例可能包含JavaScript函数执行的结果。永不归还。
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when current context is is already disposed
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the JavaScript context of the given instance is not the same as current context
        Since:
        6.9

        public boolean isFunction()
        Description copied from class: JSValue
        Indicates whether JavaScript value is a function. If this method returns true, then the value can be casted to JSFunction type. For example:

     JSFunction function = value.asFunction();
 }
